HEADWORD: Uraeus
<hw>U*rae"us</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. L.
<ets>uraeus</ets> pertaining to a tail, Gr. <?/, fr. <?/ tail.]</ety>
<fld>(Egypt. Archaeol.)</fld> <def>A serpent, or serpent's head and
neck, represented on the front of the headdresses of divinities and
sovereigns as an emblem of supreme power.</def>⟦br⟧
